Japanese Sold Net 203 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-07-13T23:53:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/japanese-sold-net-203-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended July 8 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 203 billion yen ($2.6 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 45.8 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 25.5 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 182.7 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 114.5 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 278.6 billion yen in stocks, and bought 162.1 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 326.1
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  